**AT-2: Security Awareness Training — Operational Status**

**SSP Description (from Day 51):** Annual training required before initial access and annually thereafter. Delivered via LMS. 80% passing score required. Completion tracked quarterly by ISSO. Non-compliance escalated with 10-business-day completion deadline.

**Implementation Verification:**

*Policy document:* MyClinic Security Awareness and Training Policy — current version dated [date], approved by Executive Director, signature on file. Policy reviewed within the last 12 months. ✓

*Training curriculum:* LMS training course [OpenMRS-Security-Awareness-Annual-v2] — content verified as covering all six required topic areas from the SSP description (phishing, MFA, HIPAA basics, physical security, incident reporting, social engineering). Last content review: [date]. ✓

*Completion records:* LMS export pulled for all active OpenMRS users. Findings:

| Status | Count | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Complete — current | [N] | Training within last 12 months |
| Complete — due for renewal within 30 days | [N] | Reminder sent |
| Overdue — past annual renewal date | [N] | Escalation required |
| Not completed — new hires within 5-day window | [N] | In progress |

*Discrepancy:* [N] users found with overdue training — past their annual renewal date without completion. Per the SSP procedure, ISSO should have sent a 10-business-day completion deadline notice. Review of ISSO records found that the quarterly compliance pull had not been conducted in the most recently completed quarter — the overdue status was not detected on schedule.

This is an AT-2 procedural gap: the quarterly compliance review process was not executed. The gap has two components — the immediate remediation (notify overdue users and suspend access if not completed within 10 business days) and the process gap (implement a calendar reminder to ensure quarterly compliance reviews happen consistently). Both components documented in POA&M. ISSO issued overdue notifications during today's verification.

*Verification Evidence:* Approved policy document; LMS training content with topic coverage confirmation; LMS completion export with above status breakdown; ISSO notification records for overdue users; POA&M entry for quarterly review process gap.

